The abductors of the wife of the Baba-Aso of Igboole in Igboora Local Government Area of Oyo State, Olori Funbi Ojo and her daughter have gotten in touch with the family and demanded for N4 million ransom.  LEADERSHIP reliably gathered that the abductors called the family on Tuesday evening to demand for ransom.  The duo were kidnapped by suspected Fulani herdsmen around Keji Abra farm, Igbole area of Igboora around 8:15 pm on Monday night.  A family source told the journalists that the kidnappers had on Tuesday night called the family to demand N4 million to free their captives.  They abducted wife of the monarch, who is also the matron of Oyo State College of Agriculture and Technology (OYSCATECH) Health centre while her daughter, a serving youth corps member, also works there.  It was gathered that the monarch’s wife and daughter were kidnapped while returning from the college.  However, her son who drove the bullet-ridden vehicle was said to have escaped being captured by the suspected kidnappers. 